## Suggested short presentation abstract

MMA-TP is a published protocol-level framework for structuring multi-turn LLM tutoring interactions. Rather than modifying model weights or fine-tuning the model, MMA-TP pairs an engineered runtime prompt with a JSON-based state specification that defines phases, transitions, gates, diagnostic signals, and response constraints. The protocol is designed to reduce drift, premature answer disclosure, inconsistent pacing, and loss of instructional structure. In the published evaluation, MMA-TP was compared against prompt-only tutoring baselines across 50 sessions and showed stronger preservation of phase order, guardrails, and checkpoint structure in the tested interactions.

